that are there, the plant really can't take

125
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,900
it just like that.

126
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,669
It has to exchange with the microbes.

127
00:08:20,669 --> 00:08:27,009
So, it has to catch carbon from the air, make
it into carbon sugars, pump it here, and trading,

128
00:08:27,009 --> 00:08:28,650
okay, for what it wants.

129
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:32,200
So, this is a very sophisticated marketplace
in the soil.

130
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:37,830
A handful of soil has anywhere between seven
to ten billion organisms.

131
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:43,860
So, right now, what we have done is, using
the trees, the green, whatever the material

132
